%N A397378 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} (zeta(2) - H(2*k,2))*H(2*k)/(2*k+1), where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number, and H(k,2) = A007406(k)/A007407(k) is the k-th generalized harmonic number of order 2.
%H A397378 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.32, p. 432, eq. (4.123), section 5.32, p. 464, section 6.32, pp. 661-668.
%H A397378 <a href="/index/Ha#harmonic">Index entries for sequences related to harmonic numbers</a>.
%F A397378 Equals 15*zeta(4)/32 + 7*log(2)*zeta(3)/16 - 3*log(2)^2*zeta(2)/8.
